File: Checkers said it would remove all TRESemme products from its shelves. JOHANNESBURG - Retailers Checkers and Pick 'n Pay are removing all TRESemmé products from their shelves. This follows a public outcry over a marketing campaign on the Clicks website which promoted racist stereotypes about hair. READ: TRESemmé apologises for Clicks ad Clicks removed all TRESemmé products in response to the advert. TRESemmé has apologised for the offence its campaign caused.